-- Rajaratnam Agrees to Pay $1.5 Million Disgorgement in SEC Case
-- B y   J o e l   R o s e n b l a t t
-- 2012-12-27T02:56:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-27/rajaratnam-agrees-to-pay-1-5-million-disgorgement-in-sec-case.html
Galleon Group LLC co-founder  Raj
Rajaratnam , who is serving 11 years in prison for insider
trading, agreed to pay disgorgement of about $1.5 million in a
civil case brought by the U.S. Securities and Exchange
Commission.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joel Rosenblatt in San Francisco at 
 jrosenblatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
